# Next.js Patterns

## Routes

- Pages: `app/**/page.tsx` (Server Components default)
- Layouts: `app/**/layout.tsx`
- Optional BFF: `app/api/**/route.ts` proxies to backend — not for DB

## Data fetching

```typescript
// Server Component — preferred
import { apiFetch } from "@/lib/api/client";
const data = await apiFetch<MyType[]>("/api/v1/items");
```

After client-side mutations: `router.refresh()`.

## Editable CMS pages

- Define `const relUrl = "/page-path"` matching the route
- Use `EditableText` / `EditableImage` with stable `blockKey`
- See `docs/EDITABLE-BLOCKS.md`

## Env

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` in `.env.local`

## Do not

- Add Prisma, `server/db.ts`, or direct Postgres
- Use Pages Router (`pages/` directory)
